In Paris, Van Beers began construction of a house, off the Avenue du Bois de Boulogne, where each room was to be of a different design. The project was controversial and people said that it was the work of a madman.<ref name=West/>

==Other painting==
{{section expand|date=March 2014}}
In addition to Van Beers' languid ladies, he painted a number of portraits of men, genre scenes and pictures in an [[Orientalist painting|orientalist]] style. Five hand-coloured [[Chromolithography|chromolithograph]]s of his paintings are used in the screens in [[The Flask, Hampstead|The Flask]] public house in [[Hampstead]], London.<ref name=LPG>{{cite web|title=The Flask, Hampstead|url=http://www.londonpubsgroup.org.uk/flask-hampstead|work=London Pubs Group|publisher=The Campaign for Real Ale|accessdate=6 March 2014}}</ref>
